As a bachelor in a one-bedroom flat, I have attempted to do my own cleaning – but this was not the best idea and the results were poor. For this reason, I tried the SweepSouth app. SweepSouth is an online cleaning services platform often referred to as the “Uber for cleaning services” It has proven so popular in South Africa that Naspers Foundry invested R30 million into the business in June 2019. My experience using the service was excellent, and I have outlined how it works below. To sign up to the service, you can use an email address or your Facebook profile. Once you have chosen an option and signed in, you will be greeted by the SweepSouth app home screen. This contains the “Make Booking” option, which requires you to detail the cleaning services your require. How many bedrooms and bathrooms you have in your home, what additional services you would like, and whether you will be supplying cleaning materials are the main questions you must answer. There is a list of cleaning services that are included with the base price, such as: Extras that will cost you more include: <img class="aligncenter wp-image-339066 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-640x430.jpg" alt="SweepSouth 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-640x430.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-768x516.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-1536x1032.jpg 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-2048x1377.jpg 2048w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-1-1200x807.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (ma