nce-off booking, or whether you would like to book a recurring service. There are a number of options for a recurring service, including monthly, weekly, or more frequently. Once you have set up your preferences, you then request a “SweepStar” – and SweepSouth will match you with a domestic cleaner on its platform. If you have used the platform before, an option is also available to request a previously-matched SweepStar. One of my favourite elements of SweepSouth is the regular and significant specials they offer. For example, SweepSouth recently ran a Valentine’s Day special where using the code VDAYDATE offered an R80 discount for the next clean a user booked for before 21 February. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-339078" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-Valentines-Day-640x316.png" alt="SweepSouth Valentines Day" width="640" height="316" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-Valentines-Day-640x316.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-Valentines-Day-600x296.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-Valentines-Day-768x379.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-Valentines-Day-1536x758.png 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-Valentines-Day-1200x592.png 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/SweepSouth-Valentines-Day.png 1613w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> This is by no means an uncommon occurrence – below are the emails I received from SweepSouth over 10 days. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-339080 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Sweepsouth-emails-640x141.jpg" alt="SweepSouth emails" width="640" height="141" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Sweepsouth-emails-640x141.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Sweepsouth-emails-600x132.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Sweepsouth-emails-768x169.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Sweepsouth-emails-1536x337.jpg 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Sweepsouth-emails-1200x263.jpg 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Sweepsouth-emails.jpg 1617w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Each of the SweepStars who have been matched to my cleaning requests were an absolute pleasure to work with. Professionalism, trust, and reliability are three points SweepSouth promotes as part of its service – and these were certainly delivered on. SweepSouth also includes a rating system, which works in a similar way to services like Uber. Customers are able to rate their SweepStar using a five-star ranking system once a cleaning job is complete. Additionally, you are able to add a tip from within the app. “When it comes to your home, we can truly say that our SweepStars give their best and our clients agree. All our SweepStars are experienced and trained, background checked, and in-person interviewed,” said SweepSouth.